            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          },
          "plain_text": "We stroll down the road to a Mexican restaurant. I order a local beer (Corona) mixed with Worcester sauce - which Felix teaches us how to pronounce properly - salt, chilli and other delicious spices. I order the enchiladas and share an amazing aubergine and halloumi taco with Jordan. We have a lovely conversation that skirts topics of Mexico, South Africa, London and then non spatially related topics such as children, working and other funny things. ",
