      "rich_text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": {
            "content": "We take a stroll back after eating our fill. Slowly wind down for bed and climb into a large double bed with two cats that reside in the room. The cats are separated from the almost world like dogs by two “airlocks” in the form of child proof gates on two sets of doors (the dogs often rush through one set and the second is necessary to stop them getting to the cats). The cats are named Arm Band and Percy. I immediately get their names wrong but find calling them “Hand Bag” and “Purse” - quite cute. ",
            "link": null
          },
